<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-15T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-15T20:00:00-05:00" n="588" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/181: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-15T19:00:00-06:00">June 15, 1931—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 16—11:50 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>127. I returned to Tegucigalpa today after a very worthwhile trip on the
                            north coast. Arranged with the Captain of the <hi rend="italic">Richmond</hi> and Consuls about evacuating Americans and other
                            protection measures in event of danger. Conferred with Consular
                            Inspector Davis.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>